Aida Bamia is professor emeritus of Arabic language and literature at the University of Florida in Gainesville. Currently, she is an Arabic language and literature professor at the University of Michigan. [1] She was the editor of Al-Arabiyya,[2] the journal of the American Association of Teachers of Arabic,[3] and the author of The Graying of the Raven: Cultural and Sociopolitical Significance of Algerian Folk Poetry (AUC Press 2001).[4] 
